div3.p:
Coins of Sidon (312/1) and Ake (311/0) provide the evidence
                     for interment c. 310–305, the date of both Newell and Jenkins. Nash prefers the later date, c. 305. Since the Asia Minor material above was minted before the death of Philip III,
                     there is no chronological significance in its inclusion in the hoard.92
